          "summary": "Works at the interface of machine learning and fluid mechanics: physics-constrained neural networks and reservoir computing for predicting chaotic flows, adjoint-based sensitivity and data assimilation for thermoacoustic instabilities in aeroengines, and uncertainty-aware digital twins of reacting flows. Recent projects develop stability-preserving ML surrogates and real-time flow reconstruction from sparse sensors. An exact match for students targeting ML-augmented fluid dynamics.",
