          "summary": "Studies environmental turbulence with high-resolution simulation: large-eddy and direct numerical simulation of urban boundary layers and city-scale heat and pollutant dispersion (uDALES), the physics of turbulent entrainment in plumes, jets, and gravity currents, and mixing in stratified flows. Recent projects connect urban microclimate simulation to building design and climate adaptation. Bridges engineering CFD and atmospheric boundary-layer science.",
